	<item>
		<title>Senjafuda</title>
		<pubDate>Fri, 27 Jun 2025 10:20:00 +0900</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">6B57B450-20EC-4B90-9ECC-1E41DB859CC3</guid>
		<link>https://lmnt.me/blog/sketchbook/senjafuda.html</link>
		<dc:creator>Louie Mantia</dc:creator>
		<description><![CDATA[
			<p>Nob got me「るい」<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Senjafuda">千社札</a> <small>(senjafuda, votive slips)</small> recently. I stuck them on my phone and umbrella. I asked the owners of a restaurant I go to a lot if I could stick my senjafuda on the counter where I usually sit.「いいよ！」<small>(Sure!)</small></p>
			<div class="chat">
				<cite class="friend">Nob</cite>
				<blockquote class="left">Love it.</blockquote>
				<blockquote class="left">That’s proof of a regular customer.</blockquote>
			</div>
			<hr>
			<p>You see, senjafuda are historically stuck on shrine torii or temple buildings. Nowawdays, they’re for your own things, but it also may be <strong>sometimes acceptable</strong> to stick them at other places you frequent. <small>(Ask first if you’re not 100% sure!)</small> </p>
			<p>Predictably, I’ve become <strong>obsessed</strong> with designing my own. I started with simple black-and-white versions, but pivoted to mini illustrations inspired by 浮世絵 <small>(ukiyo-e, woodblock prints)</small>.</p>
			<p>Nob is my biggest champion when I draw Japanese things. After the first day of this fixation, he lent me a great reference book for historical styles.</p>
			<p>I drew <strong>over 50</strong>, but here's some of my favorites.</p>
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/sketchbook/senjafuda.webp">
			<p>Some of these exhibit quirky characteristics like the double-wide one, or the four-up which includes a double-wide piece. Or an intentionally silly spelling of my name using hiragana, katakana, and kanji. Some have self-referential senjafuda inside of them, and one even has several「るる」, which is what <a href="https://lmnt.me/blog/photos/shichi-go-san.html">Nikki</a> calls me, sometimes in rapid succession.</p>
			<p>As an icon designer who has dabbled in making fonts too, it makes total sense to me why I would be so interested in something like this. I love a specific canvas size to play in, and I love making endless variations of things. I can <strong>easily</strong> see how this could become a lifelong hobby.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>浅草橋：マンティア「ジュニア」</li>
				<li><strong>Emoji:</strong> ジュニア</li>
				<li><strong>Hanafuda:</strong>るい 万ティア「ジュニア」</li>
				<li><strong>Signboard:</strong> ジュニア <small>(signboard)</small></li>
				<li><strong>Nickname:</strong> るる</li>
				<li><strong>Kites:</strong> あゆ、のぶ、吉、あも、る</li>
				<li><strong>Lantern:</strong> ジュニア</li>
				<li><strong>Rain Man, Tengu:</strong> ルイ・マンティア「ジュニア」</li>
				<li>ジュニア「浅草橋」</li>
				<li><strong>Nobori:</strong> ルイ・マンティア・ジュニア</li>
				<li><strong>Hanami:</strong> ルイ「ジュニア」</li>
			</ul>
			<hr>
			<p>If you like this, you can <a class="button donate" href="https://donate.stripe.com/eVag0g952cl90aQ9AA">make a one-time donation</a>, <a href="https://patreon.com/LouieMantia">donate monthly</a>, or buy something from my <a class="button" href="https://lmnt.me/shop/">shop</a>.</p>
		]]></description>
