	<item>
		<title>Three Little Moments</title>
		<pubDate>Mon, 23 Jun 2025 09:35:00 +0900</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">F63A397D-3458-45DC-9A1E-A295627455AA</guid>
		<link>https://lmnt.me/blog/three-little-moments.html</link>
		<dc:creator>Louie Mantia</dc:creator>
		<description><![CDATA[
			<p>At a yōshoku restaurant with the fami, I ordered a classic: <strong>ketchup-fried spaghetti</strong>. Instead of the typical sausage, this one arrived with shrimp. And I don’t eat seafood.</p>
			<p>Nikki <small>(8)</small> knows this and volunteered to eat them. When I picked up Tabasco, Daikichi <small>(11)</small> warned it’ll be too spicy for Nikki. Every time I found a shrimp, Nikki nabbed it. And as she ate the last one, she said it’s safe to use Tabasco now.</p>
			<hr>
			<p>One of the café staff asked about a candy bar he’s never had, <strong>Butterfinger</strong>. They’re impossible to find in Japan. Later that day, my friend Todd conveniently asked if he could bring anything from America. A few days later, I presented the express-imported Butterfinger to the café staff.</p>
			<p>When I sat at the counter a couple days later, he presented me with an almond chocolate bar he likes,「丸かじり小枝」.</p>
			<hr>
			<p>This morning when taking out the trash, I bumped into Nob’s dad <small>(75)</small>. He comes out with a <strong>Keith Haring New York</strong> shirt, looking at me wearing a <strong>髭文字「龍虎」</strong>shirt.</p>
			<p>There’s a moment I think about a fair bit from Kill Bill, where Hanzo speaks to Beatrix in the attic, “Funny. You like samurai swords. I like baseball.”</p>
