		<description><![CDATA[
			<audio controls src="https://lmnt.me/files/audio/gravitational-pull-of-reeses.m4a" preload="metadata"></audio>
			<p>I was roaming the underground shopping area outside Tokyo Station, and walked past a miniature Don Quixote, a discount shop. The normal size one is almost intolerable, so I never ever go there.</p>
			<p>As I walked by, I saw an orange bag with a Reese’s logo on it, and I finally understood what Peter Arnell was on about with the <a href="https://archive.org/details/pepsi-arnell-021109/page/n25/mode/2up">gravitational pull of Pepsi</a>, because my body involuntarily shifted into the shop. But upon closer inspection, it was actually a bag of Reese’s Dipped Pretzels, which is not at all what I wanted. I was gutted. It’s impossible to find peanut butter cups. No other Reese’s product existed in the entire store. How could this happen to me?</p>
