			<p><small>That question mark for <em>Odyssey</em> is because the O is a globe.</small></p>
			<p>Here are some initial observations:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Though the first two instances had a <strong>green</strong> M, it was used only once more, for <em>Mario Tennis Aces</em> in 2018.</li>
				<li>The most common color to be used <strong>twice</strong> in Mario’s name is <strong>green</strong> <small>(17 times)</small>, followed by <strong>red</strong> <small>(11 times)</small>.</li>
				<li>The first time any logo had <strong>five different colors</strong> was <em>Super Mario Advance</em> in 2001.</li>
			</ul>
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/mario/super-mario-advance.webp">
			<p>Let’s look at the total count per letter, per color to see what more we can learn.</p>
			<table>
				<tr>
					<th>Color</th>
					<th>M</th>
					<th>A</th>
