					<td>4</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			<p>Despite red being the most common <strong>color</strong> for the letter M, one of the most common <strong>sequences</strong> doesn’t have one. Most instances where the Mario logo begins with a blue M, it is this <strong>exact</strong> sequence. Notable examples of this sequence are <em>Super Mario 64</em> and both <em>Super Mario Galaxy</em> titles.</p>
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/mario/super-mario-64.webp">
			<p>Is <strong>this</strong> sequence in the running for the “most Mario”? Hard to say. Because another way to look at it is to find the most common sequence of the first <strong>four</strong> letters.</p>
			<table>
				<tr>
					<th>M</th>
					<th>A</th>
					<th>R</th>
					<th>I</th>
					<th>O</th>
