		<description><![CDATA[
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/sketchbook/sho-chiku-bai.webp">
			<p>It’s the new year, and there are 🎍 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kadomatsu">kadomatsu</a> everywhere. These decorations always have pine and bamboo, but there are also usually some floral element like plum blossoms. Together, these three plants are called shōchikubai, which derives from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Friends_of_Winter">“three friends of winter”</a> concept commonly found in old Chinese paintings.</p>
			<p>A reminder that you can purchase my Japanese flower cards which feature these three plants. <a href="https://buyolympia.com/Category/Junior-Hanafuda">There are three editions and a box set containing two.</a></p>
