	<item>
		<title>Nintendo</title>
		<pubDate>Mon, 11 Nov 2024 21:10:00 +0900</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">E451C9A5-6C44-4937-B490-CEFA4D908432</guid>
		<link>https://lmnt.me/blog/sketchbook/nintendo.html</link>
		<dc:creator>Louie Mantia</dc:creator>
		<description><![CDATA[
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/sketchbook/nintendo-mine.webp">
			<p>Like many of you, I have looked at the modern Nintendo logo for decades. There were many that came before it, but not many variations lately. Which is fine; I think they solidified on what was good for them. But over that time, I developed a perspective about lettering and type design. So—<em>just for fun</em>—I wanted to redraw it to meet the sensibilities I have without making any drastic changes that most people would notice. They don’t need a rebrand, but if they ever did, I would want it to be like this.</p>
			<hr>
			<p>For comparison’s sake, here’s the original, again followed up by mine to inspect the differences more closely.</p>
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/sketchbook/nintendo-real.webp">
			<img src="https://lmnt.me/files/images/sketchbook/nintendo-mine.webp">
			<p>As you can see, I’ve made the mark a smidge bolder, while making the pill shape thinner. The round characters are a little rounder. When round shapes meet vertical stems like in the n and d, the stem tapers a tiny bit to give it some clarity. The aperture of the n is also a little narrower to match the space inside the e, d, and o.</p>
			<p>I think it retains the character of the mark while tidying it up a little. I’m not saying I “fixed” it. This is just me thinking visually.</p>
			<hr>
			<p>If you like this, you can <a class="button donate" href="https://donate.stripe.com/eVag0g952cl90aQ9AA">make a one-time donation</a>, <a href="https://patreon.com/LouieMantia">donate monthly</a>, or buy something from my <a class="button" href="https://lmnt.me/shop/">shop</a>.</p>
