	<item>
		<title>Steve’s Badge</title>
		<pubDate>Mon, 28 Oct 2024 19:15:00 +0900</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">AFB7B0FF-68D8-4E7D-BAD7-6A41EC17C343</guid>
		<link>https://lmnt.me/blog/steves-badge.html</link>
		<dc:creator>Louie Mantia</dc:creator>
		<enclosure url="https://lmnt.me/files/audio/steves-badge.m4a" type="audio/x-m4a" length="251435" />
		<description><![CDATA[
			<audio controls src="https://lmnt.me/files/audio/steves-badge.m4a" preload="metadata"></audio>
			<p>Steve Jobs was notorious for not following rules. He drove his car without plates. He parked in the handicap spot at Infinite Loop. Many people assumed he didn’t use a badge.</p>
			<p>But he did. I can personally attest that he carried a badge. While almost every employee had it pinned or on a lanyard, Steve kept his in his wallet. When badging in, he took out his wallet and held it to the reader.</p>
			<p>After seeing him do it repeatedly, I started doing the same. Only one security person ever took issue with it.</p>
