		<pubDate>Tue, 09 Apr 2024 21:00:00 +0900</pubDate>
		<guid>https://lmnt.me/blog/why-by-hand.html</guid>
		<link>https://lmnt.me/blog/why-by-hand.html</link>
		<dc:creator>Louie Mantia</dc:creator>
		<description><![CDATA[
			<p>I encourage <a href="https://lmnt.me/blog/how-to-make-a-damn-website.html">making websites</a> <strong>by hand</strong> for two reasons:</p>
			<ol>
				<li>To learn what a website—at its minimum—really is.</li>
				<li>To be independent from any system or service.</li>
			</ol>
			<p>Will you make mistakes? <a href="https://lmnt.me/blog/inconsequential-mistakes.html">Sure.</a> Will it be frustrating? <a href="https://lmnt.me/blog/nothing-to-show-for-it.html">Sure.</a> But hand-writing my site is so rewarding. I’m able to post and edit so <a href="https://lmnt.me/blog/recap.html">frequently</a> because I <strong>enjoy</strong> the process.</p>
			<p>When people say I should do things differently, I think about how quickly and easily I post, and I honestly can’t see how it could be any better.</p>
		]]></description>
